The UN Convention against Corruption is the only legally binding universal anti-corruption instrument, and a unique tool for developing a comprehensive response to a global problem.

The vast majority of United Nations Member States are parties to the Convention.Â 

Ahead of a conference in Abu Dhabi, to discuss issues relating to the Convention, John Brandolino, Director of the Division of Treaty Affairs for UNODC, spoke to Elena Vapnitch-naya of UN News, and told her that he is encouraged by the way that thinking about corruption has evolved. --UNNews--